text.p: The U.S. Treasury said its Dutch auction of $12.50 billion of 5-yr notes produced a high yield of 6.325 percent and it awarded 55 percent of bids at the high.
The interest rate on the notes will be 6-1/4 percent.
The median yield was 6.300 percent and the low yield was 6.240 percent.
A total of $29.181 billion in bids was received. Treasury said it received $326 million in noncompetitive bids.
The bid to cover ratio was 2.33. The bills will be issued Oct 31 and mature Oct 31, 2001.
The high yield was down from the 6.409 at the last auction of 5-year notes on Sept 26 and was the lowest since 6.279 percent on April 24.
